  "elapsed_s": 12.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he, himself, only saw his oldest-- his oldest brother in the Italian front, where the pie-- the Py-vay-- Pi-vay River-- or Piave, as is the-- Hungarian pronounce it.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Just flipped him, it swept him away.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Andrew.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The first son-- usually in-- in Hungarian it takes [INAUDIBLE], to the mother, and-- and the boy after the-- after the father.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Lidia Enyedi-- her second name.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Her maiden name.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Her family is from Transylvania-- where the first-- the ancient Hungarians, when they moved into the Carpathian base, there was the first settlement in that area in the present-day Transylvania.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So the first Hungarians there, it goes back to some 1,400-- 1,400 years.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, her father, when they moved out from Transylvania into-- uh, into Hungary, into the place in Northeastern Hungary, the province of Scabolz-- where then I was born, her father became the bellman, as they called it in the Calvinist church.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And there she was the daughter of-- of-- of that man, but they were sort of enlightened people, so to say, because the part they came from, from Transylvania, was the birthplace of the Hungarian-- Hungarian literature, Hungarian culture-- places like [NON-ENGLISH], [?",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Chloe ?] they call it in Romania.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And [NON-ENGLISH]-- so that [NON-ENGLISH], and it became a family name, also.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And that-- that's how my, uh, my family-- my family name on the mother's side became Enyedi.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Oh--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, that's-- [LAUGHS] almost-- almost a comical thing, then.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My father, he's the age of 21, he was a-- he was a-- how do you call this tradesman?",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The-- uh, when you finish your apprenticeship, and then you become a road-- not roadman, so-something like that.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And uh, then he reached the age of 21, then he was in a military age.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
